<br>
Flatliners - Someone else mentioned this one.  Was creepy when I saw it in the theatre, still creepy years later on DVD.<br>
<br>
Nightmare on Elm Street (the first one, not any of the sequels).<br>
<br>
The Exorcist - again, the original, not the sequels.<br>
<br>
Omen - ditto<br>
<br>
The Ten Commandments - yeah, the special effects are cheesy by modern standards, but this is still good, old-fashioned, Wrath of God type stuff that really makes you take notice.  The Angel of Death/Passover thing frightened me outright when I was a kid, and it's still sort of shocking now.<br>
<br>
Most shocking movies - these movies aren't scary per se, but generate that same kind of rush due to shocking scenes, good cinematography and a suspenseful story:<br>
<br>
Alien<br>
Aliens<br>
Fatal Attraction<br>
The Thing - John Carpenter's version with Kurt Russel<br>
<br>
Books that were shocking or frightening but were made into lame-ass movies that were stupid/ridiculous/funny:<br>
<br>
It - Pennywise just never made the transition to film.<br>
<br>
Pet Sematary - Filmmakers made a mockery of this terribly frightening book.<br>
<br>
The Tommyknockers - This book was shocking, but the film was just lame.<br>
<br>
Amityville Horror - Among the most terrifying books I have ever read, the movie was just flat-out stupid.<br>
<br>
The Keep - A mediocre movie from a shocking book.  I think my issue here was that the movie showed the monster and it wasn't as scary as the monster I had imagined. <p><center><img src=http://www3.sympatico.ca/pdcowan/sig.jpg alt="Beware, Plush Cthulhu is watching!"><br><br><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=585673">Magelo</a></center></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#102960><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub169.ezboard.com/bmtboards.showUserPublicProfile?gid=brytar1>Brytar1</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Giant Squishies in Rathe</span><br>  Posts: 239<br> <font color=#628CBC>(2/25/03 12:38:04 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub169.ezboard.com/fmtboardsfrm5.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=417.topic&index=35>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: ...</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>The Tommyknockers - This book was shocking, but the film was just lame.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
